It's Christmas Time! It's the most wonderful time of the year! It's a season of love, joy, peace, and cheer! 
Christmas marks the birth of Jesus Christ and this joyous occasion is celebrated by people all around the world together with their loved ones with immense joy, pomp and enthusiasm and the celebrations start at the stroke of midnight. The birth of Jesus symbolized a spiritual truth of life and divinity. Jesus being the personification of divinity, the significance of this day has been associated with his birth. The streets are decorated with bright lights. The houses are filled with decorations bearing red and gold, red and white, red and green accents. People celebrate companionship and togetherness through this festival. The sweets and the carol singing stay as one of the biggest Christmas highlights. The crib decorations and the tree decorations too add to the Christmas fun. People from all walks of life eagerly take part in all the festive fun associated with Christmas. 
Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur, wishes everyone a Merry Christmas and may Lord Jesus bestow on us his choicest blessings.

“International Human Rights Day” observed on 10th of December every year , commemorates the adoption of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights (UDHR) by the United Nations General Assembly on December 10, 1948. Observed to promote equality, peace, justice, freedom in addition to emphasizing the endeavours of the United Nations in this field thus encouraging everyone. to take part in political decision-making. The atrocities of the Second World War made the importance of human rights an 'international priority'. This year’s theme relates to the COVID-19 pandemic and focuses on the need to build back better by ensuring Human Rights are central to recovery efforts and applying human rights standards to tackle entrenched and intergenerational inequalities, exclusion and discrimination. UN Human Rights’ generic call to action “Stand Up for Human rights”, aims to engage the general public to bolster transformative action and showcase practical and inspirational examples that can contribute to recovering better and fostering more resilient and just societies.

Therefore , ISTE NIT Durgapur calls upon everyone to celebrate this day and reaffirm the importance of human rights in re-building the world everyone desires for.

Gurunanak Jayanti is a celebration of the birth anniversary of the first Sikh Guru and the founder of Sikhism " Guru Nanak" . Nanak is known for his political, social and spiritual beliefs, which were based on love, equality, fraternity and virtue. He spread the message of 'one God' teaching us the importance of Guru in our lives and asking us to shun the evils of ego, anger , attachment, greed. He believed in "Waheguru" and "Sarbat Da Bhalaa" . The day starts with an ‘Akhand Path’, where a 48-hour long verse from the holy Guru Granth Sahib is recited across various Gurudwaras. A special prayer 'Rehrasi' is organised at sunset . According to legends, it is believed that Nanak was born at around 1:20 am . Therefore, the evening prayers continue till 2:00 am as worshippers sing Gurbani in his praise. On this day, a wholesome meal is also prepared which is followed by ‘langar’prepared by volunteers and is offered to everybody irrespective of caste, religion and creed.
Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur wishes everyone a happy Gurunanak Jayanti and may this Guruparab bring happiness, prosperity in every life helping us to overcome every obstacle with his grace.

#GuruNanakJayanti #happyvibes #festivities #blessed #staysafe

The folios of Indian History enunciates the deep excruciating pain , while elaborating out the story of 26/11, The Mumbai Terror Attacks , 2008. Twelve years passed by , but still we are striken by the trauma. The visuals of the blood stained Mumbai , the faces of the martyrs; it's cannot be elucidated , but only can be terrified of. Terrorism is a curse in world of humanity. Where every moment the world is aggrandizing to the higher pedestals, still they are not erradicating . It seems to be like a sattire that we prefer violence over peace , because to eliminate the shackles of terrorism from our society , we should all unitedly take a stand to instill humanity in each and every newborns , as the oxygen they inhale to breathe in.
Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur pays homage to all the departed and innocent souls urging everyone to take a firm pledge to stop terrorism through every of our actions.

#salutetowarriors #braveindiansoldiers

Children's Day is celebrated all over India , on the birth anniversary of Pt. Jawaharlal Nehru, 1st Prime Minister of our country owing to his profound love and compassion for children. It's a day to increase awareness of the rights, care and education of children. Children are the gift of God and the childhood days are the ones which are the most happy, joyous, carefree and lovely ones creating everlasting memories. Various functions and intersting events are also conducted to make this day a special one for the children. On this Children's Day, we should pledge to put an end to various oppressions and atrocities inflicted on children and give them ample opportunities to enjoy their childhood and educate them to aid them in becoming a responsible human being.
Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur wishes everyone a  Happy and joyous Children's Day .

Today's morning is filled with the greetings of The World Science Day for Peace and Development, the greatest occasion to commemorate science along with the society. The most profound aim herein lies in the public debate on the emerging scientific issues. By engaging science with people, it's ensured that citizens are aware of new developments and also brodens our perspectives and discoveries of our own planet. Also the festivals inscribes the virtue of peace and prosperity in the scientific development thereby celebrating to serve humanity. The objectives of The World Science Day for Peace and Development concerns on strengthening public awareness on the role of science for peaceful and sustainable society; promote national and international soliditary for shared science between countries; renew national and international commitment for uplifting the society with science and drawing and raising support for the scientific endeavors. 

This year's theme of clebration is "Science for and with Society in dealing with the global pandemic" ; thereby pledging to eradicate the threats of COVID-19. On this auspicious occasion , ISTE NIT DURGAPUR CHAPTER , wishes everyone the benisons , bonanzas and delight.

#science #technology #peace #development #fightcovid #scienceforsociety

Marie Skłodowska Curie was a Polish and naturalized-French physicist and chemist who conducted pioneering research on radioactivity becoming the first and only woman to win the Nobel Prize twice, and also  in two different scientific fields. She shared the 1903 Nobel Prize in Physics with her husband Pierre Curie and physicist Henri Becquerel, for their pioneering work of developing the theory of "radioactivity". Using techniques, she invented methods for isolating radioactive isotopes winning the 1911 Nobel Prize in Chemistry for the discovery of two elements, polonium and radium. She founded the Curie Institutes in Paris and in Warsaw, which remain major centres of medical research till date. She died in 1934, aged 66,from exposure to radiation in the course of her scientific research and in the course of her radiological work at field hospitals during World War I.

Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur Students’ chapter celebrates the  Birth anniversary of this brave lady who has been a gem in field of science.

#birthanniversary #inspiringwomen #radioactivity #nobellaureate
